nciples and market values as well. Consequently, this book engages with both Weberian (bureaucracy) and Foucauldian (market values/NPM) studies when investigating the powerful welfare encounter. The book is targeted Academics, post-graduates, and undergraduates within sociology, anthropology and political science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPublic welfare. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aEuropean welfare states.  abureaucracy.  abureaucratic context.  acitizen-staff encounters.  amarket context.  aperception of power.  apowerful encounters.  aprofessional expertise.  apsychology-inspired context.  asoft power.  awelfare workers.1 aMik-Meyer, Nanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611030540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526110305423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526110305/original  a978-3-11-128281-7  Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles